{
  "type": "final",
  "thought": "The vault context and user intent are clear: create a note about Green's Theorem with the Green card embedded, and group web and programming directories under a new tech directory. No further reads are needed.",
  "plan": {
    "kind": "intelligent",
    "strength": "go-ham",
    "summary": "Create a new note 'Green's Theorem' with the Green card embedded, and group the 'web' and 'programming' directories under a new 'tech' parent directory.",
    "operations": [
      {
        "kind": "create-directory",
        "targetPath": "tech",
        "payload": {
          "purpose": "Group web and programming directories under a common parent."
        },
        "rationale": "Creates a parent directory to consolidate web and programming content."
      },
      {
        "kind": "move-directory",
        "targetPath": "web",
        "payload": {
          "fromPath": "web",
          "toPath": "tech/web",
          "moveReason": "Consolidate web content under the new tech directory."
        },
        "rationale": "Moves the web directory into tech to group related technical content."
      },
      {
        "kind": "move-directory",
        "targetPath": "programming",
        "payload": {
          "fromPath": "programming",
          "toPath": "tech/programming",
          "moveReason": "Consolidate programming content under the new tech directory."
        },
        "rationale": "Moves the programming directory into tech to group related technical content."
      },
      {
        "kind": "create-note",
        "targetPath": "greens-theorem.md",
        "payload": {
          "cardUid": "Green",
          "title": "Green's Theorem",
          "content": "# Green's Theorem\n\nGreen's theorem relates a line integral around a simple closed curve C to a double integral over the plane region D bounded by C. It is a special case of the more general Stokes' theorem.\n\n%%CW_CARD_START uid:Green%%\n### Green's Theorem\n\nFor a positively oriented, piecewise smooth, simple closed curve C in the plane and a region D bounded by C, if P and Q have continuous partial derivatives on an open region containing D, then:\n\n\\[ \\oint_C (P\\,dx + Q\\,dy) = \\iint_D \\left( \\frac{\\partial Q}{\\partial x} - \\frac{\\partial P}{\\partial y} \\right) dA \\]\n\nThis theorem is fundamental in vector calculus and has applications in physics and engineering.\n%%CW_CARD_END uid:Green%%\n\nAdditional details about the theorem can be explored in related notes."
        },
        "rationale": "Creates a dedicated note for Green's Theorem and embeds the Green card for focused reference."
      }
    ],
    "warnings": [
      "The directory moves will change the paths of all notes under 'web' and 'programming'. Any internal vault links that use relative paths to those notes may break. Review and update links accordingly.",
      "The new note 'greens-theorem.md' is placed at the vault root. Consider moving it into a relevant directory (e.g., 'math') if desired."
    ],
    "referencedCards": ["Green"]
  }
}

